Insurance Cost Prediction Problem Statement¶

The insurance cost prediction problem involves developing a model that can accurately predict the cost of insurance premiums for individuals based on various factors such as age, gender, medical history, charges, and other relevant information.

The objective of this problem is to build a predictive model that can help insurance companies determine the risk associated with an individual and set premiums accordingly. The model should be able to accurately predict insurance costs for new customers based on their individual characteristics, as well as help insurance companies identify and manage high-risk customers.

To solve this problem, the data scientist will need to collect and preprocess the relevant data, explore the data to identify any patterns or correlations, select appropriate features, and build and test various machine learning models to identify the best-performing model for this task. The model's accuracy will be evaluated based on metrics such as mean squared error, mean absolute error, and R-squared.

Deseription¶

The objective of this insurence dataset is to predict charges the datsets consists of several predictor variables and one target variable

Data Pre-processing¶

Converting categorical variable to numerical variable

Apply get dummies method

this is one of the approch and an each one of the encode catagorical data pandas get_dummies() method takes catagorical feature as argument then it creates a dummy variable for verey labele in the feature such that each dummy variable holds data as 1 or 0. 1 indicates the presence of particular label and 0 indicates the absence of particular label

For example if feature contains lables as male and female after applying pandas get_dummies ()to the feature Dummy variable for both male and female labels are created

Bulilding optimal model using Backward Elimiation Method¶

when we are buliding a machine learning model it is very importnt we select only those features or predictors which are necessary suppose we have 50 feature or predictors on our dataset that dose not necessary mean that we need to have all 50 feature in our model there are verious ways in which you can find out which feature have very littel impact on the model and which ones you can remove from your dataset

A similar idea can be applied in Backward Elimiation weather a feature significantly impacts the output or not A p-value helps detemine weather a hypothosis must be accepred of rejected
